{"id": "EUVD-2024-52033", "enisaUuid": "3f041d81-88d2-3883-a3b4-229b6a4b86f9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnilfs2: prevent use of deleted inode\n\nsyzbot reported a WARNING in nilfs_rmdir. [1]\n\nBecause the inode bitmap is corrupted, an inode with an inode number that\nshould exist as a \".nilfs\" file was reassigned by nilfs_mkdir for \"file0\",\ncausing an inode duplication during execution.  And this causes an\nunderflow of i_nlink in rmdir operations.\n\nThe inode is used twice by the same task to unmount and remove directories\n\".nilfs\" and \"file0\", it trigger warning in nilfs_rmdir.\n\nAvoid to this issue, check i_nlink in nilfs_iget(), if it is 0, it means\nthat this inode has been deleted, and iput is executed to reclaim it.\n\n[1]\nWARNING: CPU: 1 PID: 5824 at fs/inode.c:407 drop_nlink+0xc4/0x110 fs/inode.c:407\n...\nCall Trace:\n <TASK>\n nilfs_rmdir+0x1b0/0x250 fs/nilfs2/namei.c:342\n vfs_rmdir+0x3a3/0x510 fs/namei.c:4394\n do_rmdir+0x3b5/0x580 fs/namei.c:4453\n __do_sys_rmdir fs/namei.c:4472 [inline]\n __se_sys_rmdir fs/namei.c:4470 [inline]\n __x64_sys_rmdir+0x47/0x50 fs/namei.c:4470\n do_syscall_x64 arch/x86/entry/common.c:52 [inline]\n do_syscall_64+0xf3/0x230 arch/x86/entry/common.c:83\n entry_SYSCALL_64_after_hwframe+0x77/0x7f", "datePublished": "2025-01-11T12:35:40", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T20:48:23", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/55e4baa0d32f0530ddc64c26620e1f2f8fa2724c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5d4ed71327b0b5f3b179a19dc3c06be9509ab3db", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/912188316a8c9e41b8c1603c2276a05043b14f96", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ef942d233643777f7b2a5deef620e82942983143", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/284760b320a0bac411b18108316939707dccb12b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ff561987ff12b6a3233431ff659b5d332e22f153", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/901ce9705fbb9f330ff1f19600e5daf9770b0175", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53690", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00001.html", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/03/msg00002.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53690"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "20616c65-6102-379c-a730-297b335925f5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d25006523d0b9e49fd097b2e974e7c8c05bd7f54 <912188316a8c9e41b8c1603c2276a05043b14f96"}, {"id": "36f5dac2-2414-34ed-a494-9b5749fcb271", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.7"}, {"id": "588184d9-0500-3aea-b4f9-5ae170bd20d9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "5937f478-e129-38ae-a6f5-d3587a4ca8df", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d25006523d0b9e49fd097b2e974e7c8c05bd7f54 <ef942d233643777f7b2a5deef620e82942983143"}, {"id": "61b7a3dd-ee02-327d-b09a-2bb713e69fd9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.176"}, {"id": "656560a3-5c9e-3bdd-893c-cfef8a969f55", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.122"}, {"id": "6b043dad-2b7f-344f-8aa2-21b053960fa1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "2.6.30"}, {"id": "7080c913-7662-39bd-86de-f6b610fe601d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13"}, {"id": "74b780a7-67f5-3149-9b0c-5a2404bd325d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.233"}, {"id": "7510bfec-2546-3d3e-bc21-b2984a917d0d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d25006523d0b9e49fd097b2e974e7c8c05bd7f54 <5d4ed71327b0b5f3b179a19dc3c06be9509ab3db"}, {"id": "83839485-96ec-3c6d-91aa-a6ffbda52d61", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d25006523d0b9e49fd097b2e974e7c8c05bd7f54 <ff561987ff12b6a3233431ff659b5d332e22f153"}, {"id": "84ba4fd6-72dc-3be5-8669-d04f15330a6f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.289"}, {"id": "e1be9458-c5f4-36d2-a0cb-1018a0e4700b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "d25006523d0b9e49f